data.title: Cushman & Wakefield's Q3 2025: 9% service fee revenue growth, 4th consecutive quarter of double-digit Capital markets revenue.
data.description: In New York, Cushman & Wakefield (NYSE: CWK) released its financial results for the third quarter of 2025. The company highlighted significant growth, with a 9% increase in service line fee revenue. This marks the fourth consecutive quarter of double-digit growth in Capital markets revenue. Additionally, organic Services revenue saw a surge, rising to 7%. The company attributes this growth to its transformational strategy.

data.title: REGENXBIO finishes pivotal enrollment and starts commercial production in Duchenne Gene Therapy Program, with patients showing significant improvements.
data.description: In the Phase I/II part of the AFFINITY DUCHENNE® trial, patients receiving RGX-202 treatment displayed steady and strong microdystrophin expression along with enhanced functionality. The observed improvements surpassed those seen in the natural progression of the disease. This outcome suggests a promising possibility for approval through the accelerated approval pathway. REGENXBIO is actively enrolling participants in further stages of the trial.

data.title: Dream Finders Homes reported Q3 2025 results: $917M homebuilding revenues, 1% increase in closings to 1,915, 20% rise in new orders to 2,021.
data.description: Jacksonville-based Dream Finders Homes, Inc. (NYSE: DFH) revealed its financial performance for Q3 2025, ending on September 30. During this quarter, homebuilding revenues totaled $917 million, marking a decrease from $986 million in Q3 2024. However, home closings saw a 1% rise, reaching 1,915 compared to 1,889 in the same period last year, setting a new third-quarter high for the company. Moreover, net new orders surged by 20%, hitting 2,021 in Q3 2025 from 1,680 in Q3 2024.

data.title: Builders FirstSource reports $3.9 billion net sales in Q3 2025, 6.9% decrease due to lower core sales and commodity deflation.
data.description: In Irving, Texas, Builders FirstSource, Inc. (NYSE: BLDR) released its third-quarter results for the period ending September 30, 2025. The key highlights of the quarter include net sales of $3.9 billion, marking a 6.9% decline from the previous year. This drop was influenced by reduced core organic net sales and commodity deflation, although it was partially offset by gains from acquisitions. The gross profit margin also saw a significant decrease of 240 basis points, falling to 30.4%, mainly due to challenging market conditions resulting in a below-average starts environment.

data.title: Zachry Group wins EPC contract for NiSource's Combined Cycle Generation Project.Characters: 65
data.description: Zachry Group, based in San Antonio, has recently secured the Engineering, Procurement, and Construction (EPC) contract for NiSource's Combined Cycle Generation Project. This contract award marks a significant milestone for Zachry Group as they continue to expand their portfolio in the energy sector. The project is expected to create numerous job opportunities and drive economic growth in the region. This achievement highlights the company's expertise and capabilities in the industry.

This move marks a pivotal moment for Onex as it seeks to capitalize on new opportunities for expansion and value creation.

data.title: Honeywell completes spin-off of Solstice Advanced Materials, now trading as "SOLS" on Nasdaq. Automation and Aerospace separation on track for completion by second half of 2026.
data.description: Today, Solstice will start trading on Nasdaq with the ticker symbol "SOLS". This spin-off further progresses Honeywell's strategy to establish three distinct market leaders. Their plan to separate the Automation and Aerospace businesses is on schedule and expected to be finalized in the latter half of 2026.

data.title: Foundation Medicine partners with Manifold to implement AI in drug discovery, using FoundationInsights®.
data.description: Foundation Medicine has recently collaborated with Manifold in a pioneering move to integrate artificial intelligence (AI) technology into FoundationInsights®. This partnership aims to enhance the analytical capabilities of FoundationInsights®, providing a cutting-edge solution that leverages AI for improved data interpretation and insights. This collaboration signifies a significant step forward in the utilization of AI in healthcare, showcasing the commitment of Foundation Medicine and Manifold to innovation and advanced analytics. This integration is expected to revolutionize data analytics in the medical field, potentially impacting numerous patients and healthcare providers.

data.title: Insmed's Q3 2025 financial report: BRINSUPRI earns $28.1M revenue, approved for non-CF bronchiectasis treatment in U.S. and EU.
data.description: BRINSUPRI ™ (brensocatib) has been granted approval by the FDA as the initial and sole treatment available for Non-Cystic Fibrosis Bronchiectasis. The positive opinion from CHMP has been accepted in the European Union, and the application is under review in Japan. In the third quarter of 2025, BRINSUPRI has generated a total revenue of $28.1 million.

data.title: DTE Energy reports Q3 achievements: executed 1.4GW data center agreement, invested $3B so far, on track to invest $4.4B by 2025.
data.description: A 1.4 gigawatt data center agreement has been executed, aiming to bring substantial affordability benefits for current clients. There will be a continued significant investment in enhancing reliability and shifting towards cleaner energy generation. The company is scheduled to invest $4.4 billion in its utilities by 2025. Additionally, nearly $3 billion has already been invested in various initiatives to support these goals.

data.title: Fermi America™ partners with Mobile Power Solutions for 157.5 MW via GE TM2500 Turbines, part of a 500 MW project to be live in 2026, establishes a 20-year strategic partnership. America's largest private energy grid gains more power.
data.description: A strategic agreement has been made between Fermi America and Mobile Power Solutions to advance the Project Matador's initial 500 MW generation capacity, set to come online by 2026. This agreement spans 20 years and marks the beginning of a significant partnership in the US energy sector. The collaboration aims to support America's energy resurgence and secure the future of the country's biggest private grid campus.

data.title: Indivior Q3'25 revenue: Total $314m (+2% YOY), SUBLOCADE® $219m (+15% YOY). ROW business discontinued, expects $150m savings in 2026.
data.description: In the third quarter of 2025, the company reported a total net revenue of $314 million, showing a 2% year-over-year increase. Specifically, the net revenue for SUBLOCADE® in Q3'25 was $219 million, marking a 15% growth compared to the previous year. The company also revealed the decision to optimize its Rest of World (ROW) business and announced the cessation of sales and marketing support for OPVEE®. This strategic move is expected to result in annual operating expense savings of at least $150 million in 2026. Overall, the company is on track to meet its financial objectives.

data.title: Vulcan Materials Company reports strong Q3 2025 results with earnings growth and margin expansion across all segments, promising 2026 growth.
data.description: In the latest financial report, Vulcan Materials Company (NYSE: VMC) based in Birmingham, Alabama, highlighted robust earnings growth and margin expansion across all segments in 2026. The company experienced improved demand, leading to continued expansion in aggregates unit margins. The performance indicates solid execution of strategies, with significant growth in key financial indicators. These achievements position Vulcan Materials Company as a leading player in the construction industry, displaying a strong financial outlook for the foreseeable future.

data.title: SiriusXM's Q3 2025 results released, available on their website at https://investor.siriusxm.com.
data.description: SiriusXM revealed its operational and financial performance for Q3 2025, with detailed earnings accessible on the Investor Relations page of their website. The company's stock is listed under NASDAQ as SIRI. For more information, visit https://investor.siriusxm.com.

data.title: Conexiant unveils MDspire, AI-driven platform for healthcare pros. Transforms clinical knowledge consumption.
data.description: In Tampa, Florida on October 30, 2025, Conexiant has launched MDspire, an innovative AI-driven platform aimed at revolutionizing how doctors, researchers, and healthcare professionals access clinical information. This platform is set to address concerns related to content overload and provide a more efficient way for users to engage with clinical knowledge.

data.title: PST Group signs €141M contract to build Rheinmetall factory in Baisogala, Lithuania, largest defense industry investment.
data.description: A contract worth €141 million (including VAT) has been secured by the PST Group for the development of the Rheinmetall Defence Lithuania factory complex in Baisogala, Radviliškis district. This investment marks the largest in Lithuania's defense industry to date.
